WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.220
[Amit Varma]: It sometimes seems both amusing and sad how many people behave as if they are the masters

00:00:11.220 --> 00:00:16.340
[Amit Varma]: of the universe. I see this both at an individual level and at the level of the species. It

00:00:16.340 --> 00:00:21.880
[Amit Varma]: reminds me of when Douglas Adams famously said, quote, Imagine a puddle waking up one

00:00:21.880 --> 00:00:26.240
[Amit Varma]: morning and thinking, this is an interesting world I find myself in, an interesting hole

00:00:26.240 --> 00:00:32.560
[Amit Varma]: I find myself in, fits me rather neatly, doesn't it? In fact, it fits me staggeringly well,

00:00:32.560 --> 00:00:37.880
[Amit Varma]: must have been made to have me in it. This is such a powerful idea that as the sun rises

00:00:37.880 --> 00:00:43.360
[Amit Varma]: in the sky and the air heats up, and as gradually the puddle gets smaller and smaller, is still

00:00:43.360 --> 00:00:47.540
[Amit Varma]: frantically hanging on to the notion that everything's going to be all right because

00:00:47.540 --> 00:00:52.320
[Amit Varma]: this world was meant to have him in it, was built to have him in it. So the moment he

00:00:52.320 --> 00:00:57.280
[Amit Varma]: disappears catches him rather by surprise. I think this may be something we need to be

00:00:57.280 --> 00:01:02.480
[Amit Varma]: on the watch out for. Stop quote. This is a familiar attitude. We are on the top of

00:01:02.480 --> 00:01:06.840
[Amit Varma]: the food chain of mammals. We seem to have conquered the world and we strut around like

00:01:06.840 --> 00:01:12.640
[Amit Varma]: perpetually signaling peacocks. But seen from another lens, we could just be useful vehicles

00:01:12.640 --> 00:01:18.040
[Amit Varma]: for the true masters of the universe, bacteria colonized by them and used as an end to their

00:01:18.040 --> 00:01:23.960
[Amit Varma]: means. And even if we were top dog, humans have existed for a tiny fraction of the time

00:01:23.960 --> 00:01:28.720
[Amit Varma]: the universe has been around. And we will surely stop existing one day as the universe

00:01:28.720 --> 00:01:35.080
[Amit Varma]: continues freed from distracting social media chatter. But as I point out that human existence

00:01:35.080 --> 00:01:40.320
[Amit Varma]: is utterly insignificant and meaningless. I shall also concede that one thing does set

00:01:40.320 --> 00:01:46.800
[Amit Varma]: us apart from other species, our level of self awareness. We are the only bot designed

00:01:46.800 --> 00:01:52.560
[Amit Varma]: with the capability to edit our own source code and reprogram ourselves. The fact that

00:01:52.560 --> 00:01:59.280
[Amit Varma]: we are able to do this is one small step towards controlling our own destiny. And it also ought

00:01:59.280 --> 00:02:04.080
[Amit Varma]: to fill us with humility. After all, even if we are a self aware puddle, a puddle is

00:02:04.080 --> 00:02:16.960
[Unknown]: what we are and puddles vanish. Welcome to the scene and the unseen, our weekly podcast

00:02:16.960 --> 00:02:22.160
[Amit Varma]: on economics, politics and behavioral science. Please welcome your host, Amit Bharma. Welcome

00:02:22.160 --> 00:02:26.600
[Amit Varma]: to the scene and the unseen. My subject for today is genetics, and I intend to explore

00:02:26.600 --> 00:02:31.480
[Amit Varma]: the science of it, the ethical questions that arise from the ability to reprogram ourselves

00:02:31.480 --> 00:02:36.360
[Amit Varma]: and others and the policy implications of all of this. And my guest is a scholar well

00:02:36.360 --> 00:02:42.400
[Amit Varma]: placed to comment on all three aspects. Dr. Shambhavi Naik is a biologist who also runs

00:02:42.400 --> 00:02:48.040
[Amit Varma]: her own startup and is a fellow at the Takshashila Institution. I've been trying to get her on

00:02:48.040 --> 00:02:52.540
[Amit Varma]: my show for a couple of years now, but the stars never aligned. But with the supreme

00:02:52.540 --> 00:02:58.200
[Amit Varma]: control of the universe that humans possess, we got the stars to align. And here she is.

